# TOKENIZATION RULES

## Source of Truth
Use `docs/compression_map.md` as the canonical mapping. Every identifier (functions, types, fields, errors) must follow the map. Do not invent new compressed names — extend the map if needed, then use it.

## Naming Conventions
- Functions: prefix `f` + number (e.g. f14, f49)
- Types/structs: prefix `t` + number
- Fields: prefix `s` + number
- Error variants: prefix `E` + number on the app error enum
- Parameters: prefix `p`; locals: prefix `v`

## Preserved (not compressed)
Rust std types, primitives, traits, ecosystem crate types (Router, SqlitePool, etc.), axum extractors, HTML/CSS/JS content strings.

## Allow Attribute
Crate root uses `#![allow(non_camel_case_types, non_snake_case, dead_code, unused_imports)]` for tokenization. Other files inherit. No other warning suppression — fix root cause.

## Documentation
Comment compressed → readable when helpful: `/// f14 = encrypt_token`
